Average path length (L) refers to the mean distance between two nodes, which is averaged over all pairs of nodes. Diameter (D) is the maximum distance between any pair of nodes. Clustering coefficient (C) is the ratio of all existing edges between the neighbors and the maximum number of edges possible between these neighbors [26]. C is defined as following:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
