Three centrality indices of nodes in the pathway-based protein association network were further evaluated, including degree centrality (C
d), betweenness centrality (C
b) and closeness centrality (C
c). C
d is the proportion of other nodes adjacent to a node. C
b is the total number of shortest paths going through a node. C
c is the number of other nodes divided by the sum of the distances between a node and all the other nodes. The equations are listed as follows:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
